// Derived-Move in action. This array is placed in an agent-shared region
// (dma_shared has a DMA agent) with no `@dma` adjective. `apply_derived_move`
// wraps it in `Type::Dma` at resolution because the region is concurrently
// mutated, so the rvalue index-read below is rejected with E326 -- the same
// protection a hand-written `@dma` gives, now derived from placement (usage
// dictates declaration). See region.rs::apply_derived_move.
var BUF: [u32; 4] @align(4) in dma_shared;
fn main() @context(thread) {
    BUF[0] = 1;
    var x: u32 = BUF[0];
    BUF[1] = x;
}
